# This is a personal list of steps to install a nice and clean Linux environment

Install Manjaro (xfce edition)!

# Packages to install :
git vim cscope strace i3 i3status-manjaro dmenu dropbox skype eh htop yaourt chromium chromium-pepper-flash 

# Configuration files to add/replace :
~/.iconfig/i3/config
/etc/vimrc
/usr/share/vim/vim74/plugin/cscope_maps.vim
/usr/share/vim/vimfiles/colors/molokai.vim # visual color is edited

# Manual session changes :
In xfce4-settings-manager > startup & session:
Add an entry for i3
Remove xfwm4, xfce4-panel, xfdesktop, close all apps and save session

# Bootloader configuration edit :
Set GRUB_TIMEOUT to 0 in /etc/grub.d/00_header
Generate and use grub config : grub-mkconfig > /boot/grub/grub.cfg

# Visual settings :
In appearance settings, use everything Adwaita, Cantarell 10 fonts
In terminal, use Deja Vu Sans Mono 10
Set background with lightdm-gtk-greeter-settings (as root), use images with read permissions and set theme too
